## Welcome

The Cornell University Center for Advanced Computing ([CAC](https://www.cac.cornell.edu/)) is a leader in the development and deployment of
Web-based training programs. Our Cornell Virtual WorkshopSM learning platform is designed to
enhance the computational science skills of researchers, accelerate the adoption of new and emerging technologies,
and broaden the participation of underrepresented groups in science and engineering. Over 350,000 unique visitors
have accessed Cornell Virtual Workshop training on programming languages, parallel computing, code improvement,
and data analysis. The platform supports
learning communities around the world, with code examples from national systems such as
[Frontera](https://www.tacc.utexas.edu/systems/frontera),
[Stampede2](https://www.tacc.utexas.edu/systems/stampede2), and
[Jetstream2](https://jetstream-cloud.org/).

**To Get Started:** Select the [Roadmaps](/Roadmaps/) tab. Roadmaps
are grouped by category. Each roadmap consists of about 5-10 topics that are listed in a suggested order.
You are welcome to skip to whatever topic you like.
View the FAQ or request [consulting help](/help).
Your [Notebook](/notebook)
allows you to view your completed items, past consulting questions, and page notes.

**Downtime:** Downtime for regular Web server maintenance will occur the Wednesday following the second Tuesday of every month. The outage will usually
be less than 30 minutes.